WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:42.070 --> 00:01:46.270
Luffy vs. Commander Cracker

3
00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:46.250
Hmph! What an insolent brat!

4
00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:50.420
Look at this sword! Isn't it something?

5
00:01:50.420 --> 00:01:55.680
It's called Pretzel!
It's a one-of-a-kind sword!

6
00:01:55.680 --> 00:02:00.160
I'll teach you a lesson
about the roughness of the New World!

7
00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:05.520
What?! A one-of-a-kind sword?!
But you've got six!

8
00:02:07.850 --> 00:02:09.600
Let's run for now, Luffy!

9
00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:11.780
No way!

10
00:02:12.220 --> 00:02:14.000
Gear Third!

11
00:02:16.790 --> 00:02:19.260
Gum-Gum...

12
00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:22.800
Elephant Gun!

13
00:02:33.920 --> 00:02:37.630
You fools have got nowhere to run!

14
00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:43.640
Damn!

15
00:02:59.850 --> 00:03:03.090
Pretzel Roll!

16
00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:41.260
That's my brother!

17
00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:42.490
Luffy...

18
00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:01.510
Oh, no!

19
00:04:01.510 --> 00:04:06.350
They're members of an emperor's crew!
We underestimated them!

20
00:04:06.450 --> 00:04:10.310
Even Luffy's having a hard time
with her underling!

21
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:13.350
Luffy! Run!

22
00:04:16.060 --> 00:04:17.610
W-What the...?

23
00:04:20.030 --> 00:04:24.320
Stop there! I'll deal with you two!

24
00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:26.370
Me too!

25
00:04:47.760 --> 00:04:52.220
I know how you feel.
You just got scared, didn't you?

26
00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:57.600
The Worst Generation?
What's so "worst" about it?!

27
00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:01.530
After being puffed up
in the first half of the Grand Line,

28
00:05:01.530 --> 00:05:05.820
lots of crews have come here and been certain
that their captain would be pirate king,

29
00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:09.080
only to be disappointed by the result.

30
00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:11.240
I've witnessed it firsthand!

31
00:05:11.950 --> 00:05:18.790
In the past two years, many of them have come wandering into Mama's territory.

32
00:05:18.790 --> 00:05:21.000
"Captain" Kid.

33
00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:22.980
"Roar of the Sea" Apoo.

34
00:05:22.980 --> 00:05:24.780
"Gang" Bege.

35
00:05:24.780 --> 00:05:27.550
"Mad Monk" Urouge.

36
00:05:27.550 --> 00:05:33.470
Aside from Bege, who wisely realized he was out of his depth and joined our crew,

37
00:05:33.470 --> 00:05:41.320
the rest were all tossed out, without ever getting to see or speak to Mama!

38
00:05:41.870 --> 00:05:45.020
The only one to make any progress was...

39
00:05:45.020 --> 00:05:47.760
Mad Monk Urouge!

40
00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:53.540
He was impudent enough to defeat
one of the Sweet Commanders!

41
00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:57.290
They were the Four Sweet Commanders
until not so long ago.

42
00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:00.830
But that's as far as he got.

43
00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:04.840
Mama was furious,
and sent Cracker to crush him!

44
00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:07.630
He had nowhere to run!

45
00:06:07.630 --> 00:06:11.580
I bet he's dead in a ditch right now!

46
00:06:18.540 --> 00:06:19.600
She disappeared!

47
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:31.620
Listen!

48
00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:35.450
This is your brick wall in the New World.

49
00:06:41.920 --> 00:06:46.570
Trying to fight the Four Emperors? You must be dreaming!

50
00:06:46.570 --> 00:06:49.320
You'll never even see Mama!

51
00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:53.850
Infiltrate the tea party?
Stop the wedding?

52
00:06:53.850 --> 00:06:59.270
Taking your crewmate back?!
All of that is a dream!

53
00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:05.150
You have no hope of even catching sight of Mama's face! You will die in this forest!

54
00:07:07.650 --> 00:07:10.320
M-My Tact...

55
00:07:12.910 --> 00:07:17.040
Now, come to the Mirro-world!

56
00:07:18.380 --> 00:07:20.620
Let go of me!

57
00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:26.130
Come on! Come on! Come to me!

58
00:07:26.130 --> 00:07:30.600
I'll have plenty of time to cut up your face and body in here!

59
00:07:31.510 --> 00:07:32.800
Pound-chan !

60
00:07:36.840 --> 00:07:38.930
Just give up!

61
00:07:38.930 --> 00:07:41.310
Let go of her, Brûlée!

62
00:07:53.460 --> 00:07:55.280
Thank you!

63
00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:57.280
Father Pound!

64
00:07:57.280 --> 00:08:01.410
No, it's just Pound, now!
What you've just done is treason against Mama!

65
00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:05.080
You're a dead man! No one will save you now!

66
00:08:15.420 --> 00:08:17.750
Thunderbolt...

67
00:08:17.750 --> 00:08:19.260
Tempo!

68
00:09:00.430 --> 00:09:03.560
Brûlée will come back.

69
00:09:03.560 --> 00:09:09.400
She can show up in any place that has a mirror.

70
00:09:09.400 --> 00:09:12.110
I'm sorry. You did it to help me!

71
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:19.030
I was targeted to be killed anyway.

72
00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:21.530
By my ex-wife.

73
00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:28.790
By the way, are you Lola's friend?

74
00:09:28.790 --> 00:09:29.900
Uh-huh.

75
00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:43.910
I see. It's no mistake!

76
00:09:43.910 --> 00:09:47.170
Lola's mama is Big Mom.

77
00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:53.530
The fact that those trees in the forest
are afraid of this vivre card proves it.

78
00:09:54.280 --> 00:09:58.450
I'll make good use of it, Lola!

79
00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:24.640
Oh, no! We'll get involved!

80
00:10:36.820 --> 00:10:41.900
Hey! Don't get so spread apart that you forget your Seducing Woods duties!

81
00:10:41.900 --> 00:10:44.910
There must never be an exit to the woods!

82
00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:47.660
O-Okay!

83
00:10:47.660 --> 00:10:49.960
Block his way!

84
00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:07.430
Gum-Gum...

85
00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:12.890
Hawk Gatling!

86
00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:14.840
Hard Biscuit!

87
00:11:21.110 --> 00:11:25.530
Damn!
His Armament is too hard!

88
00:11:49.100 --> 00:11:54.690
If you consider Vinsmoke Sanji to be a friend,
then leave him alone.

89
00:11:54.690 --> 00:12:00.400
He's a prince of a mighty kingdom.
His status is far greater than yours!

90
00:12:02.490 --> 00:12:07.120
He will have a proud wife and live here...

91
00:12:07.910 --> 00:12:10.700
with his every desire catered to!

92
00:12:16.010 --> 00:12:22.340
You selfishly claim you will take back your friend,
rather than allowing him to be happy?

93
00:12:22.340 --> 00:12:26.040
When his annoying former captain finds him,

94
00:12:26.040 --> 00:12:30.390
that proud prince will no doubt say...

95
00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:39.070
"Begone from my sight, 
you miserable, lowlife pirate!"

96
00:12:56.520 --> 00:12:58.420
Muscle Balloon!

97
00:13:24.820 --> 00:13:27.000
Gear Fourth!

98
00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:29.580
Boundman!

99
00:13:32.240 --> 00:13:35.710
Muscle Balloon is a good name.

100
00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:41.950
But what can a balloon do?

101
00:13:43.300 --> 00:13:45.510
Let me say it one more time!

102
00:13:45.510 --> 00:13:48.890
Begone from my sight, you miserable, lowlife pirate!

103
00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:03.600
Gum-Gum...

104
00:14:03.600 --> 00:14:04.340
Kong...

105
00:14:04.340 --> 00:14:06.220
Hard Biscuit!

106
00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:08.270
Gun!

107
00:14:27.080 --> 00:14:29.800
Minister Cracker!

108
00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:36.430
Don't insult Sanji!

109
00:14:36.430 --> 00:14:40.020
Even if he's happy
and doesn't want to come back,

110
00:14:40.020 --> 00:14:44.440
he'd never talk to us like that!

111
00:14:56.600 --> 00:14:59.500
I'm gonna go see Sanji!

112
00:15:00.860 --> 00:15:02.770
Gum-Gum...

113
00:15:03.120 --> 00:15:05.460
Don't push your luck!

114
00:15:07.420 --> 00:15:08.820
Pretzel...

115
00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:10.280
Kong Gun!

116
00:15:10.280 --> 00:15:11.900
Roll!

117
00:15:17.680 --> 00:15:20.710
Minister Cracker!

118
00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:41.620
What?!

119
00:15:45.980 --> 00:15:49.050
You did a good job breaking...

120
00:15:49.050 --> 00:15:51.300
my armor!

121
00:15:56.970 --> 00:15:58.890
Who are you?!

122
00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:01.350
Who am I?

123
00:16:02.250 --> 00:16:06.110
I'm pretty sure I already introduced myself as Sweet Commander Cracker.

124
00:16:06.100 --> 00:16:11.110
"Thousand Arms" Cracker

125
00:16:15.570 --> 00:16:17.920
I really liked that armor...

126
00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:21.160
Armor?
No way! He coughed up blood!

127
00:16:21.160 --> 00:16:23.870
– That was jam!
– Jam?!

128
00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:28.090
Since I'm a craftsman at heart,
I also make sure that it tastes good.

129
00:16:30.330 --> 00:16:34.590
I'm a biscuit man 
with the powers of the Bis-Bis Fruit!

130
00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:39.010
I can produce and manipulate an infinite number of biscuits!

131
00:16:47.520 --> 00:16:49.650
To shape them into anything...

132
00:16:50.770 --> 00:16:52.800
Crush Biscuit!

133
00:16:59.710 --> 00:17:02.100
And if I craft it carefully...

134
00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:08.670
Look! It's the face of a hardened warrior!

135
00:17:10.960 --> 00:17:13.210
The form that biscuits have taken

136
00:17:13.210 --> 00:17:16.890
has changed throughout history, depending on the baker.

137
00:17:17.890 --> 00:17:22.140
Very few people have forced me to reveal my true identity.

138
00:17:23.630 --> 00:17:28.260
Just look at the picture on my wanted poster, which was issued by the World Government.

139
00:17:28.260 --> 00:17:31.690
It's not me. It's my armor!

140
00:17:34.230 --> 00:17:39.450
I despise pain. I can't even 
stand the prick of a needle!

141
00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:44.910
And that's why I use my armor to fight.

142
00:17:44.910 --> 00:17:50.540
When I clap my hands, they multiply.
That is the power and beauty of my biscuits!

143
00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:54.420
I have unlimited power at my disposal!

144
00:17:55.800 --> 00:17:59.180
You had to give your all to defeat...

145
00:17:59.180 --> 00:18:05.810
a biscuit soldier that I can remake over and over.

146
00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:11.360
Do you understand now why you will never see
Vinsmoke Sanji again?

147
00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:15.690
I will definitely return.

148
00:18:23.620 --> 00:18:26.620
I'm gonna see Sanji!

149
00:18:32.340 --> 00:18:37.520
Learning that there are people you can't beat
no matter the effort you put in

150
00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:41.430
is a mark of true growth, brat!

151
00:18:48.770 --> 00:18:50.230
I'll teach you a lesson!

152
00:19:06.160 --> 00:19:09.910
– We can't do it!
– We have no chance!

153
00:19:09.910 --> 00:19:12.170
Run!

154
00:19:22.020 --> 00:19:24.800
I guess we'll be safe here.

155
00:19:24.800 --> 00:19:27.850
We're no match for him!

156
00:19:27.850 --> 00:19:29.390
I'm here.

157
00:19:43.120 --> 00:19:45.370
When did she get there?!

158
00:19:46.790 --> 00:19:50.370
If you close your mouth,
you'll be sealing your doom.

159
00:19:52.230 --> 00:19:58.920
Even if all of you shriveled up 
and withered away, I wouldn't care at all!

160
00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:01.880
What?!

161
00:20:01.880 --> 00:20:05.260
You're a horrible person.

162
00:20:05.260 --> 00:20:10.420
Sweet Commander Cracker,
or his mother, Emperor Big Mom.

163
00:20:10.420 --> 00:20:12.500
Which is scarier?

164
00:20:12.500 --> 00:20:14.440
You're scarier than both of them!

165
00:20:19.520 --> 00:20:22.570
Brûlée's Mirro-world

166
00:20:30.650 --> 00:20:35.880
I see! I get the picture!
Listen, Carrot!

167
00:20:36.520 --> 00:20:42.260
I have a great idea,
so from now on, please call me Big Bro Chopper!

168
00:20:43.010 --> 00:20:44.680
Uh-huh, okay.

169
00:20:44.680 --> 00:20:45.840
Good!

170
00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:49.140
And what is your idea, Chobro?!

171
00:20:49.140 --> 00:20:51.100
Chobro?!

172
00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:55.440
That's right!
Short for Big Bro Chopper, Chobro!

173
00:20:56.810 --> 00:20:59.150
Well, okay.

174
00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:01.840
It seems like this world of mirrors

175
00:21:01.840 --> 00:21:05.640
is connected to all of the mirrors
on Whole Cake Island!

176
00:21:05.640 --> 00:21:08.160
Yes, I think you're right.

177
00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:13.410
Instead of escaping from here,
we should take advantage of Brûlée's ability!

178
00:21:13.410 --> 00:21:14.960
How?

179
00:21:14.960 --> 00:21:18.500
We can look for Sanji through these mirrors!

180
00:21:18.500 --> 00:21:21.300
You're right! That's my Chobro!

181
00:21:22.910 --> 00:21:27.590
Your compliment doesn't 
make me happy, you jerk!

182
00:21:28.170 --> 00:21:32.660
The Capital (Sweet City)
Whole Cake Island

183
00:21:39.640 --> 00:21:42.550
Secret Song: Whirlwind Slash!

184
00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:01.920
– That went well.
– Mm-hm.

185
00:22:01.920 --> 00:22:06.380
After it's done patrolling, the biscuit soldier will return to the castle storage room.

186
00:22:06.380 --> 00:22:08.340
We'll wait until then to make a move.

187
00:22:28.870 --> 00:22:33.870
I'll beat you up and go see Sanji!

188
00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:04.520
Gum-Gum...

189
00:23:04.520 --> 00:23:05.630
Kong...

190
00:23:07.100 --> 00:23:10.300
Organ!

191
00:23:14.820 --> 00:23:15.660
Advance!

192
00:23:40.220 --> 00:23:41.790
Honey Pretzel!

193
00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:56.300
♪ It's morning! It's morning! ♪

194
00:23:53.420 --> 00:23:55.800
Good morning!

195
00:23:55.800 --> 00:24:00.160
Today, the Vinsmoke family will be coming to the castle,

196
00:23:56.300 --> 00:24:00.160
♪ Good morning! ♪

197
00:23:59.440 --> 00:24:02.980
Whole Cake Chateau

198
00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:02.950
♪ It's morning! It's morning! ♪

199
00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:02.960
and we'll hold an engagement ceremony, Mama.

200
00:24:02.950 --> 00:24:07.630
♪ It's a new morning again! ♪

201
00:24:02.960 --> 00:24:05.920
What about the wedding cake?

202
00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:07.630
That comes tomorrow.

203
00:24:10.840 --> 00:24:13.510
It's been one night.

204
00:24:13.510 --> 00:24:16.640
How are the mold spores holding up?

205
00:24:16.640 --> 00:24:19.840
This is their last chance
to make contact with their friend.

206
00:24:19.840 --> 00:24:24.940
Oh, please! How could you say that
after you sent Minister Cracker?

207
00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:31.280
It's true that once Black Leg enters the castle,
their chances of contact are essentially zero!

208
00:24:31.280 --> 00:24:36.240
After all, both the tea party and the wedding
will be held in the castle.

209
00:24:36.240 --> 00:24:40.290
So they're all talk? Just like the others?

210
00:24:40.290 --> 00:24:44.240
Some of the Vinsmoke sons
aren't here yet, right?

211
00:24:44.240 --> 00:24:46.130
Oh, actually,

212
00:24:44.950 --> 00:24:49.480
The Kingdom of Germa

213
00:24:46.130 --> 00:24:49.480
I just received word that they have landed at the port.

214
00:24:51.380 --> 00:24:53.380
Good. They're here.

215
00:24:53.380 --> 00:24:56.470
My beloved sons!

216
00:24:56.470 --> 00:25:00.060
I can't wait to see them face off with Sanji.

217
00:25:17.940 --> 00:25:20.030
Welcome back!

218
00:25:24.240 --> 00:25:29.520
Vinsmoke "Sparking Red" Ichiji
Eldest Son of the Vinsmoke Family

219
00:25:34.790 --> 00:25:40.080
Vinsmoke "Electric Blue" Niji
Second Son of the Vinsmoke Family

220
00:25:43.790 --> 00:25:47.600
– Prince Ichiji! Prince Niji!
– Nice to see you back from your long trip!

221
00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:51.520
I can't believe that you ended the
long war on Broc Coli.

222
00:26:05.540 --> 00:26:08.940
Why isn't he coming out to greet us?

223
00:26:08.940 --> 00:26:10.590
Give it a rest, Niji.
